content: Great app that i have been using for a long time.

I am the admin for a Facebook group focused on viewing the Northern Lights 
in the Lake Superior region and host a popular Northern Lights web site. 
After evaluating many of the paid versions of Aurora Borealis forecast 
apps, this is the app I am recommending to our 1,900+ members. The app 
presents forecast data in a concise, easy to read manner. The app does 
provide some non relevant data, and I wish it also contained the most 
recent 24 to 48 hours of Kp readings, but I still gelt this app was the 
easiest to use, read, and updated frequently. Just as importantly when I 
reached out to the developer by email with questions and suggestions, he 
responded quickly in a polite manner. Good app. Purchase the pro version 
and support the developer. Ditch the ads, but the free version also 
performed well.
Amazing app have been using it for year

replyContent: Hi, the difference is that the pro version does not have ads in it. My apologies for this not being clear. If you would like a refund, please e-mail me at jake@jrustonapps.com and I'll be happy to provide one.

Highly responsive developer. As a new aurora hunter I had questions re using this app, what the info means to me in my location. Jake took the time to answer every question I had in a manner I was able to understand.  Think of this app as providing info similar to severe weather watches here on Earth, which tell us to pay closer attention to the weather. I had not made that connection prior to Jake's response. So much makes sense now that I've connected those dots! While not all local weather watches become warnings, they do tell us to be alert because something might happen. This app provides that heads up type of info.  And remember Kp numbers are worldwide. I had not accounted for that fact (duh!) so a high number may not mean much to me if it is issued during daylight hours in my location but it could mean folks on the dark side of the planet might be in for a show.   Many, many thanks, Jake! Two thumbs up!
